item.description:
ConvertTo-DataTable Convert an object (list) to a data table.
Syntax &lt;Object&gt; | ConvertTo-DataTable [-ColumnType] &lt;HashTable&gt; Parameters [-Object] &lt;Object&gt;
The object(s) to be converted to a DataTable.
[-ColumnType] &lt;HashTable&gt;
Type definition of each column by name: @{&lt;ColumnName&gt; = &lt;Type&gt;; ...}
Examples Converting a custom object to a data table
$MyObject = @( New-Object PSCustomObject -Property @{Name = &#34;a&#34;; Value = 123; Date = $Null} New-Object PSCustomObject -Property @{Name = &#34;b&#34;; Value = 123456789012; Date = $Now} ) $DataTable = $MyObject | ConvertTo-DataTable Defining the column types:
